{
  "stem": "1860.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That-- that's now and I was happy, fortunate to be with my mother.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we tried just to-- to-- to survive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We managed on soups and bread-- rations of bread.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- we-- we managed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, as I said, when we were in Emalia this Teckla used to once in a while to smuggle someone a little bit of additional food, which-- which always helped.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the news trickled here and there, but nobody could even imagine-- until we got to Auschwitz, I could never imagine-- I could never conceive-- what a-- what a concentration camp or what an extermination camp is like.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Don't forget Plaszow was a labor camp-- forced labor camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we were there with people whom we knew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had a contact with-- with people outside of Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that-- that was bad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What was horrible was the killings, and hangings, and so on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we were sort of on our own-- on our own territory.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Fortunately not.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were just petrified of him and his two tremendous dogs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew that at his whim he could provoke them and they would just jump at-- without any reason at-- at working people, and bite and kill them at--",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, while we were going out to-- out of Plaszow to work in-- in Emalia in enamelware factory, there were-- there were Jewish so called [GERMAN] men, the policemen who were escorting us.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were also German guards.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we were going to work and this was like-- almost like a routine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Except for coming back to Plaszow and finding out what transpired during the day.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How many were killed?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And our actions when the-- when the children were taken away-- I-- I wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
